The summary of results of a bias audit of an Automated Employment Decision Tool (AEDT) must include the following information:
1. The distribution date of the AEDT;
2. The name and contact information of the independent auditor who conducted the bias audit;
3. The methodology used to conduct the bias audit;
4. The impact ratio for each category (sex, race/ethnicity, and intersectional categories);
5. The number of individuals assessed by the AEDT who are not included in the required calculations because they fall within an unknown category;
6. Any category that represents less than 2% of the data being used for the bias audit may be excluded, but the summary of results must include the independent auditor’s justification for the exclusion, as well as the number of applicants and scoring rate or selection rate for the excluded category.
